===Etymology 1===
From {{bor|en|pt|mandarim}}, {{m|pt|mandarij}}, from {{der|en|ms|menteri}}, {{m|ms|manteri}}, and its source, {{der|en|sa|मन्त्रिन्|t=minister, councillor}}, from {{m|sa|मन्त्र|t=counsel, maxim, mantra}} + {{m|sa|-इन्|pos=an agent suffix}}.

Chinese {{glossary|folk etymology}} sometimes erroneously claims that the word originates from {{m|zh|[[滿]][[大人]]|tr=Mǎndàrén|lit=Manchu important man}}.

